16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 330.99 of Title 63, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Oklahoma Task Force 1 (OK-TF1) shall be recognized as the
21 official deployment asset team for urban search and rescue missions
22 and for floods and disasters in the State of Oklahoma; provided,
23 however, OK-TF1 shall not be deployed for wildland firefighting.
24 OK-TF1 shall be the first deployed asset for any Emergency
Req. No. 16968 Page 1

1 Mana gement Assistance Compact-related requests outside of the State
2 of Oklahoma during any declared disasters.
3 B. The Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management is
4 authorized to promulgate and enforce rules governing the
5 administration, allowable uses, and oversight of the Oklahoma Task
6 Force 1 Revolving Fund.
7 C. There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving
8 fund for the Oklahoma Department of Emergency Management, to be
9 designated the "Oklahoma Task Force 1 Revolving Fund". The fund
10 shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations,
11 and shall consist of all monies deposited to the credit of the fund
12 by law. All monies accruing to the credit of the fund are hereby
13 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Department of
14 Emergency Management for the direct reimbursement of participating
15 agencies of Oklahoma Task Force 1. Expenditures from the fund shall
16 be made upon warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims
17 filed as prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of
18 Management and Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
19 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
20 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
21 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
22 Emergency Management, from any monies not otherwise appropriated
23 from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal
24 year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of _____________________
Req. No. 16968 Page 2

1 ($__ _________) to be deposited in the Oklahoma Task Force 1
2 Revolving Fund, and used by participating agencies of Oklahoma Task
3 Force 1 for the direct reimbursement of costs incurred during in-
4 state or out-of-state task force deployments.
5 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
6 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
7 There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Department of
8 Emergency Management, from any monies not otherwise appropriated
9 from the General Revenue Fund of the State Treasury for the fiscal
10 year ending June 30, 2027, the sum of _____________________
11 ($___________) to be deposited in the Oklahoma Task Force 1
12 Revolving Fund. Of those funds appropriated, the sum of
13 _____________________ ($___________) shall be dedicated and utilized
14 by the Oklahoma City team of Oklahoma Task Force 1 solely for
15 personnel, equipment, logistics, transportation, lodging, and
16 operational expenses. Funds appropriated may also be used for
17 deployment readiness and capability enhancements including training,
18 specialized equipment, communications systems, canine acquisition,
19 care and training, and other resources necessary to support disaster
20 response deployments. Appropriated funds shall not be used for
21 routine or daily fire department operations, staffing, facilities,
22 maintenance, or other expenses not related to the task force. Of
23 those funds appropriated, the sum of _____________________
24 ($___________) shall be dedicated and utilized by the Tulsa team of
Req. No. 16968 Page 3

1 Okla homa Task Force 1 solely for personnel, equipment, logistics,
2 transportation, lodging, and operational expenses. Funds
3 appropriated may also be used for deployment readiness and
4 capability enhancements including training, specialized equipment,
5 communications systems, canine acquisition, care and training, and
6 other resources necessary to support disaster response deployments.
7 Appropriated funds shall not be used for routine or daily fire
8 department operations, staffing, facilities, maintenance, or other
9 expenses not related to the task force.
10 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
